Heat Exchanger: The CAES and HCAES concepts each have a two-stage compression system with a heat exchanger after every compressor. The HCAES and the two HES concepts have one heat exchanger at the outlet of the hydrogen compressor. The costs for the heat exchangers in the compressor path are added to the compressor costs. CAES and HCAES also have a recuperator that preheats the compressed air from the cavern before it enters the HP combustion chamber. The cost of the recuperator is also determined using Eq. 4 and added to the cost of the turbine. The area of the heat exchangers AHE\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
